######
#
# Task 1
#
######

Total points: 120

In lectures/lecture-06-16/lambda5.py, we have implemented
an inference-based type-checker. Please extend this type-checker
to handle ALL language constructs present in the following
datatype [dexp]:

```
datatype dexp =
//
| DEint of sint
| DEbtf of bool
| DEstr of strn
//
| DEvar of dvar
| DElam of
( dvar, dexp(*body*))
| DEapp of
( dexp(*fun*), dexp(*arg*))
//
| DEopr of (strn, list(dexp))
//
| DEfst of (dexp)
| DEsnd of (dexp)
| DEtup of (dexp, dexp)
//
| DEif0 of
( dexp(*test*)
, dexp(*then*), dexp(*else*))
//
| DEfix of
( dvar(*fun*)
, dvar(*arg*), dexp(*body*))
//
| DElet of
( dvar(*x*)
, dexp(*def*), dexp(*scope*))
//
| DElist_nil of ()
| DElist_cons of (dexp, dexp)
//
| DElazy of dexp
| DEstcn_nil of ()
| DEstcn_cons of (dexp, dexp)
//
| DEarry_size$val of (dexp(*size*), dexp(*val*))
| DEarry_size$fun of (dexp(*size*), dexp(*fun*))
//
| DEanno of (dexp, styp(*anno*))
//
| DElam1 of
  (dvar(*x*), styp, dexp(*body*))
| DEfix1 of
  (dvar(*f*), dvar(*x*), styp(*arg*), styp(*res*), dexp(*body*))
//
```

Please note that you need to first introduce
STlist, STstrm (and STstcn), and STarry for handling
lists, streams (and stream-constructors), and arrays.

