Total points: 30

In lecture/lecture-06-08, there is an implementation
of Eratosthenes' sieve algorithm. Please translate this
implementation into LAMBDA such that the translation in
LAMBDA can pass type-checking performed by the type-checker
implemented in Task 1.

######
#
# Task 3
#
######

Total points: 50

The following simple implementation of the factorial
function can be readily encoded in LAMBDA (via the use
of DEfix):

def fact(n):
  def loop(i, r):
    return r if (i>=n) else loop(i+1, (i+1)*r)
  return loop(0, 1)

In Quiz02, Task 2 asks a translation of the above Python
implementation into Church's pure lambda-calculus (that is,
only, DMvar, DElam, and DEapp can be used). This time, you
are asked to give yet another translation of the above Python
code into Church's pure lambda-calculus such that the translation
should pass type-checking (performed by the type-checker in Task 1).

You MUST EXPLAIN the idea behind your translation (or I would not
be able to grade your solution).

